18/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Controversial businessman and wartime arms dealer Zvonko Zubak has founded a new political party called the Democratic Social Union. The 45-year-old Zubak was unanimously elected leader at the party's first congress on Sunday (17 August). He told the 101 delegates that the party platform would be aimed at returning "dignity to people", taking them from "poverty and a state of social and moral neglect . due to an irresponsible government". Zubak has said his business deals with trade in crude oil and oil derivatives and that he has a number of companies abroad. (HINA, Croatian Radio, BBC - 18/08/03)
